&lt;p&gt;Bedford Digital Collections is an online repository of primary sources that make it easy for student to do history. A rich variety of carefully selected primary sources is available as single documents or as ready-made, discovery-oriented projects crafted by leading historians. Multi-source projects are constructed to help students develop important skills of analysis and interpretation, and instructors may select and assign exactly the documents they wish to use. Instructors can also customize single documents and project by editing existing headnotes and questions or by adding their own sources and commentary.&lt;/p&gt;

